summary: Imagine: Tony’s Daughter in Avengers Endgame
title: Imagine: Tony’s Daughter in Avengers Endgame
body:
“You can’t be sure that Tony is still alive. I’m sorry, but I doubt that he is.”

“Nat, you can’t be sure that he’s dead either. I know he’s still alive. I can feel it.”

“Don’t do this to yourself. You have to accept it.”

“Steve, I’m gonna find Dad and I’m gonna bring him home.”

“Dad, if you’re out there somewhere, give me a sign. Let me know that you’re still alive, please.”

BONUS:

“Baby, I want you to know that I love you more than anything in this universe and I will see you again.”

summary: Rewatching the first Ironman, and I'm sure this has been said but. How much of Tony's change was because of Yinsen. Yes, of...
body: Rewatching the first Ironman, and I’m sure this has been said but. How much of Tony’s change was because of Yinsen. Yes, of course seeing his weapons being used against them was a huge part. But. Yinsen telling him “Don’t waste it, don’t waste it.” As he dies. I feel that stayed very close to him, and it’s something he never shares with anyone. And it becomes a driving force, not to waste his skills, to help as much as he can.

summary: JOIN THE FUN AT THE VALHALLA VIEW! Come be part of the most luxurious residential building in Manhattan. Like leaves on a tree...
caption:
JOIN THE FUN AT THE VALHALLA VIEW!

Come be part of the most luxurious residential building in Manhattan. Like leaves on a tree in Autumn, you’re guaranteed to fall for the apartments at Valhalla View! In Valhalla View residents not only get a cushy apartment and plenty of amenities but they also receive the company of their neighbors! Come be part of a community of extraordinary people and lease an apartment today.

Kosmopolites is a neighbor / city AU roleplay where your character is a resident of the Valhalla View building, an apartment building located in the heart of Manhattan. As a resident you will be able to form bonds with the other residents, pick up a job in the city, discover new things and create new adventures in the form of hangouts at the diner or lounge, romances or events in the building!

summary: Tony’s Daughter Imagines: Coming Out to Your Daughter (Stony)
title: Tony’s Daughter Imagines: Coming Out to Your Daughter (Stony)
body:
“What I’m trying to tell is that … . Steve and I are together. We’re dating. I’m dating a man.”

“Dad, I know. I saw you two making out a couple of days ago in the living room. I’m surprised your tongue didn’t pop out of Steve’s ear.”

“So what do you think? You cool with it?”

“Yeah, I’m cool with it. You’re still my dad and I love you even if you’re french kissing Captain America on the couch.”

Bonus:

“So you know about me and Tony now?”

“Yes, I do, and I fully support it, but here this, Rogers. If you ever hurt my dad, I’m gonna be the last person you see before you learn how to walk again.”

“I believe you.”
